    <p>On August 28, 2024, a severe stormed rocked the coast of Michigan. Over 350,000 people have been left without power. Damage and destruction has stricken thousands of families as they await assistance from the authorities. In addition to this untimely storm, Michigan is also currenrly experiencing an extreme heat wave. The power outages and scorching heat have had devastating effects on the community. </p>
    <p>Susan Loud, a Michigan resident, spoke to us and described the unfortuante situation.<q>This is an absolute disaster. We have never experienced such widespread devastation.     <h2>Record Breaking Heat</h2>
    <p>The heat wave that has scorched Michigan has reached record breaking temperatures. According to the Michigan heat history, <cite>Michigan has not experienced heat like this since the heat stroke of 1972. During that heat stroke temperatures reached a high of 85 degrees.</cite> Today, temperatures rose well into the 90's. This record breaking heat is having unprecedented and unexpected consequences on the surrounding communities. Authtorites have estimated that recovery will take at least two months before significant imporvemets are made in the community. Michigander's are encouraged to remain indoors as much as possible as this extensive situation eventually reaches it's denouemment.</p>
